# CLAUDE.md — {{name}}

This is a RunAgents agent project.

## Quick Start

```bash
pip install runagents
runagents dev          # Start local dev server on :8080
runagents deploy       # Deploy to the platform
```

## Project Structure

- `agent.py` — Agent handler function
- `runagents.yaml` — Agent configuration (tools, model, system prompt)
- `requirements.txt` — Python dependencies

## Agent Handler

The `handler(request, ctx)` function in `agent.py` receives:
- `request["message"]` — the user message
- `request["history"]` — conversation history
- `ctx` — RunContext with `ctx.call_tool(name, path, payload)` and `ctx.chat(message)`

Return a string or `{"response": "..."}`.

## Tools

Add tools to `runagents.yaml` then use `agent.call_tool("tool-name", "/path", payload)`.
The platform mesh handles authentication and authorization automatically.

## Deployment

```bash
runagents deploy       # Deploys from runagents.yaml
```
